              </note>
              <gloss><p xml:id='OTPSD25015159P0'>Commonly known as the Pontotoc Dragoons, Company I of the 1st Regiment, Mississippi Cavalry (Confederate) was organized on February 22, 1861 in Pontotoc County, Mississippi under the command of Capt. John E. Turner and served in the Western Theater. (Howell, Jr., <hi rend='italic'>Military History of Mississippi</hi>, 37; Rowland, <hi rend='italic'>Official and Statistical Register of Mississippi</hi>, 763)
